  Abstract                 = {In the present study we have investigated the ontogeny of FMRFamide expression in the snail,Lymnaea stagnalis, from its first appearance to its distribution in young adults.
 The first FMRFamide-like immunoreactive (FaLI) cells within CNS appear by E45 embryonic stage (premetamorphic veliger). The number of FaLI neurons increases throughout both pre- and post-hatching development.
